{
  "stem": "25598.4",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I was always active and I always liked to live in the life of the-- in eye of the tornado, not on the periphery.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And Israel certainly gives you that.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Every day of your life, you're in-- in the eye of the tornado.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I loved it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But my parents couldn't handle it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So we decided to-- to leave and to go to Montreal.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Before-- when we came back to Romania, my father gave a Romanian soldier some gold coins and stuff, and he brought Auntie Sidi back from the depth of Russia to Romania.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Then she left to Israel a lot earlier than we did.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "My grandmother died in 1953, in Romania.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Auntie Sidi was now in Israel, where she still is.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Uncle Armin and Auntie Mila and their kids lived in Montreal, and they took us out there too.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So that's how I got to Canada.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I immediately started to study.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I'd lost a lot of schooling and stuff, so I immediately-- actually, I had a master's degree from Romania.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because when I finished high school, Russian became the second language in Romania, instead of-- replacing French, which it used to be before.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they didn't have any Russian teachers.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they needed a large number of Russian teachers to supply to all the schools.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So in order to ensure that this is going to be a successful program, they went through all the schools and picked out the students who finished their matriculation with the highest grades, and put them in this institute of Russian language and literature in Bucharest, which was an intensive immersion program in Russian language and literature.",
      "word_count": 57
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I did so well.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I wanted to study medicine, but I had no choice.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
